         \pard\plain<$Scr_Ps::0>\f0\fs28\sb240\
            <term>Infrared (IR) Thermometer</term>: An IR thermometer measures temperature without direct contact with the object. It detects the infrared radiation emitted by the object, converting it into a temperature reading. IR thermometers are particularly useful for non-contact measurements or in hazardous environments.\
	\
\pard\plain<!$Scr_Ps::0>\f0\fs28\sb240\cf3
